{{distinguish|Kula language (Bantu)|Kula language (Australian)}} {{Infobox language |name=Kula |nativename=Tanglapui |region=[[Alor Island]] |speakers=5,000 |date=1997 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Papuan |fam1=[[Trans‚ÄìNew Guinea]] |fam2=[[West Bomberai languages|West Bomberai]] |fam3=[[Timor‚ÄìAlor‚ÄìPantar languages|Timor‚ÄìAlor‚ÄìPantar]] |fam4=[[Alor‚ÄìPantar languages|Alor‚ÄìPantar]] |fam5=[[Alor languages|Alor]] |fam6=East |fam7=[[Tanglapui languages|Tanglapui]] |iso3=tpg |glotto=kula1280 |glottorefname=Kula (Indonesia) }}
'''Kula''' (Kola) or '''Lamtoka''' (Lantoka), also known as '''Tanglapui''', is a [[Papuan language]] of the {{citation needed span|text=[[Moluccas]]|reason=The Ethnologue link gives Alor Island, NTT. Alor lies outside Maluku.|date=July 2017}} . Dialects are Kula proper, Kulatela, Watena, Kula Watena, Iramang, Larena, Sumang, Arumaka.
