* All of the diphthongs are rising, i.e. their second elements have more prominence.{{sfnp|Hanul√≠kov√°|Hamann|2010|p=376}}{{sfnp|Pavl√≠k|2004|p=95}}
* The phonetic quality of Slovak diphthongs is as follows:
** {{IPA|/…™ÃØ…õ/}} is typically a glide from {{IPA|/i/}} to {{IPA|/…õ/}} ({{IPA|[»ãÃû…õÃù]}}).{{sfnp|Pavl√≠k|2004|pp=96‚Äì97}}
** {{IPA|/…™ÃØa/}} is typically a glide from the position below {{IPA|/i/}} to {{IPA|/√¶/}} ({{IPA|[»áÃù√¶Ã†]}}).{{sfnp|Pavl√≠k|2004|pp=95, 97}}
** {{IPA|/…™ÃØu/}} is typically a glide from {{IPA|/i/}} to the position more front than {{IPA|/u/}} ({{IPA|[»ãÃû ä]}}).{{sfnp|Pavl√≠k|2004|pp=96‚Äì97}}
** {{IPA|/ äÃØ…î/}} is typically a glide from {{IPA|/u/}} to the position above {{IPA|/…î/}} ({{IPA|[»óÃûoÃû]}}).{{sfnp|Pavl√≠k|2004|pp=96‚Äì97}}
* There are many more phonetic diphthongs, such as {{IPA|[a äÃØ]}} in ''Miroslav'' {{IPA|[Ààmir…îsla äÃØ]}} and {{IPA|[…î äÃØ]}} in ''Pre≈°ov'' {{IPA|[Ààpr…õ É…î äÃØ]}}. Phonemically, these are interpreted as sequences of {{IPA|/v/}} preceded by a vowel. This {{IPA|[ äÃØ]}} is phonetically {{IPA|[»óÃû]}} and it is very similar to the first element of {{IPA|/ äÃØ…î/}}.{{sfnp|Pavl√≠k|2004|p=105}}{{sfnp|Hanul√≠kov√°|Hamann|2010|p=374}}

